shortcontents.shortcontent:
I) Dawit “Psalter” (fols. 1r-201ra) I-1) Mäzmurä Dawit “Psalms of David” (fols. 1r-155v) I-2) Mäḥalǝyä näbiyat “The Canticles of the Prophets” (fols. 156r-173r) I-3) Mäḥalǝyä mäḥalǝy “Song of Songs” (fols. 173r-181v) I-4) Wǝddase Maryam “Praise of Mary” (fols. 182ra-196vb) I-5) ʾAnqäṣä bǝrhan “The Gate of Light” (fols. 196vb-202ra) I-6) Mäzmurä dǝngǝl “Psalter of the Virgin” (strophes distributed between sections of Texts I-1, I-2, I-3, fols. 1r-181v)
Additiones 1-5.

donors.donor: The names of ʾAmätä Mikaʾel, Wälättä Mikaʾel, Gäbrä Mikaʾel, Wäldä Samuʾel are written in the supplications, added later in a secondary hand, fols. 10v, 20r, 42r, 51r, 172r, 180v.

owners.owner: The name of the previous owner was probably written on the missing part of fol. 1 (s. Additio 1).

txstates.txstate: The boards are missing. Quires I and II are detached from the textblock. The edges of many fols. are damaged by rodents. Many fols. are stained with water and wax.

bindings.binding: Both boards are missing. Two pairs of sewing stations.

bnothers.bnother: Small hole is visible on the spine fold of the quires, close to the head of the codex.

txfolios.txfolio: Foliation mistake: the leaf after fol. 166 has been foliated as 168.

taunit.mr-info: Texts I-1, I-2, I-3, I-6: all data are for fol. 3r.
taunit.rl-info: Pricking and ruling and are partly visible. Ruling pattern: 1A-1A/0-0/0-0/C. Primary pricks are partly visible. Ruling pricks are not visible. The upper line is written above the ruling. The bottom line is written above the ruling. The bottom ruled line was not used by the scribe on fol. 34.

taunit.mr-info: Texts I-4, I-5: all data for fol. 183r.
taunit.rl-info: Pricking and ruling are visible. Ruling pattern: 1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. Primary pricks are visible. Ruling pricks are visible (very close to the outer edge). The upper line is written above the ruling. The bottom line is written above the ruling.

margin.info: Fols. 1r-180v(Texts I-1, I-2, I-3, I-6). All data are for fol. 3r.
Fols. 181r-201r (Texts I-4, I-5). All data are for fol. 182r.

rulings.ruling: Pricking and ruling and are not visible. Ruling pattern: Text I-1, I-2, I-3: 1A-1A/0-0/0-0/C Text I-4, I-5: 1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. Primary pricks are not partly visible. Ruling pricks are not visible. Structural pricks are not visible. The upper line is written above the ruling. The bottom line is written above the ruling.

rubrications.rubrication: Name of St. Mary in Texts I-4, I-5 and I-6; name of Jesus Christ in Text I-4; name of Archangel Gabriel in Text I-5; initial line of the inscription on fol. 1r; title of Texts I-2, I-3, I-5; three groups of two adjacent lines on the incipit page of Text I-4; title and number of the Pss. and Canticles; number of the Songs; initial line of the Pss. of Text I-6; title and part of the incipit of the daily readings of Text I-4; doxology following each Song; refrains of Texts I-4 and I-5 (written out fully or abbreviated); name and traditional interpretation of the Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; a few single words in Texts I-4 and I-5; elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.

abbreviations.abbreviation: Text I-4 ሰ፤ ለ፤ ቅ for ሰአሊ፡ ለነ፡ ቅድስት Words or their abbreviations stand for the whole refrain. ሠ፡, ሠረቀ፡ for ሠረቀ፡ በሥጋ፡ እምድንግል፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ዘርአ፡ ብእሲ፡ ወአድኅነነ እስመ፡ for እስመ፡ በፈቃዱ፡ ወበሥምረቱ፡ አቡሁ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ መጽአ፡ ወአድኅነነ ኵ፡, ኵሉ፡ for ኵሉ፡ ትውልድ፡ ያስተበፅዑኪ፡ ለኪ፡ ለበሕቲትኪ፡ ኦእግዝእትነ፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ ናዓ፡ for ናዓብየኪ፡ ኵልነ፡ ኦእግዝእትነ፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ። እስመ፡ ሣህልኪ፡ ይኵን፡ ላዕለ፡ ኵልነ ለኪ፡ for ለኪ፡ ለበሕቲትኪ፡ ኦእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ እመ፡ ብርሃን፡ ናዓብየኪ፡ በስብሐት፡ ወበውዳሴ ተ፡, ተፈ፡ for ተፈሥሒ፡ ኦምልዕልተ፡ ጸጋ፡ ተፈሥሒ፡ እስመ፡ ረከብኪ፡ ሞገስ፡ ተፈሥሒ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ምስሌኪ ወ,፡ ወበ፡ for ወበእንተዝ፡ ናዓብየኪ፡ ኵልነ፡ ኦእግዝእትነ፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ንጽሕት፡ ኵሎ፡ ጊዜ፡ንስእል፡ ወናንቀዓዱ፡ ከመ፡ ንርከብ፡ ሣህለ፡ በኀበ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ ሰብእ Text I-5 ወ᎓ ሣ᎓ ይ᎓ ሰ᎓ ቅ᎓ for ወልድኪ፡ ሣህሎ፡ ይክፍለነ፡ ሰአሊ፡ ለነ፡ ቅድስት The abbreviations stand for the whole refrain. ወበ፡ for ወበእንተዝ፡ ናዓብየኪ፡ ኵልነ፡ ኦእግዝእትነ፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ንጽሕት፡ ኵሎ፡ ጊዜ፡ንስእል፡ ወናንቀዓዱ፡ ከመ፡ ንርከብ፡ ሣህለ፡ በኀበ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ ሰብእ

otherdetails.otherdetail: - Text I-1 begins with an inscription: ነዓ፡ ኀቤየ፡ ንጉሠ፡ እስራኤል። በዓለ፡ መዝሙር፡ ሠናይ፡ ወጥዑመ፡ ቃል። ታለብወኒ፡ ነገረ፡ ወፍካሬ፡ ኲሉ፡ አምሳል። ከመ፡ እወድሳ፡ ለማርያም፡ ድንግል። - The Pss. of Text I-6 are not numbered.

additional.det: The note, written in red ink, is incomplete due to the damage of the fol. Also, a part of it has been erased. It has been probably written in the main hand.
The note is very crudely written and hance hardly legible.

additional.cont: Fols. 202va-203v: Mälkəˀa Fasilädäs “Image of Fasilädäs”, incomplete.
additional.det: The prayer is written in a trained hand (possibly the same as that of the main text). Blank spaces for rubrication are left unfilled.
The note is partly unreadable due to faded ink.

extras.extra: - A part of Text I-4 on fol. 182ra, contains musical notation signs. - The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line on fols. 60v, 66v, 67r, 78v, 157r. - Omitted letters, words, lines or passages written interlineally, in the main hand and in a secondary hand: e.g., fols. 8v, 10r, 33v, 52r, 109r, 129v (rubricated), 155r, 173v, 183ra, 185va. - Corrections indicated by thin lines above and below the word: e.g., fols. 10v, 52v, 58r, 125v. - Corrections written over erasures: fols. 38r, 48v, 64v, 65r, 66r, 101v, 108v, 148v, 156v. - Erasures marked with lines: fols. 14r, 52v, 54r, 58r, 58v, 63v, 67r, 17v, 171v. - Erasures: fols. 17r, 20r. - At least two texts have been erased on fols. 202ra-202rb. - Minor notes, scribbles, writing excercises: fols. 2r, 3r, 21r, 22r, 25r, 38v, 39r, 147r, 186r, 191v, 192r, 193r, 196v, 197r, 202v.

txquiremarks.txquiremark: - Undecorated quire marks are written in the left upper and bottom margins of the fol., on the first and last fols. of the quire: fols. 1r, 8v, 9r, 16v, 17r, 24v, 25r, 32v, 33r, 40v, 41r, 48v, 49r, 57r, 64v, 65r, 72v, 73r, 80v.

txfindingaids.txfindingaid: - Daily readings of Texts I-1 and I-2 are indicated by the names of the days of the week written, in a secondary hand, in the upper margin: ዘሰኑይ: fol. 1r ዘሰሉሥ[sic]: fol. 30r ዘረቡዕ: fol. 58v ዘሐሙስ: fol. 82r ዘዓርብ: fol. 117r ዘቀዳሚት: fol. 138v ዘዕሑድ[sic]: fol. 156r.

frames.frame: - The Pss. are divided into groups of fifty separated by a line of alternating black and red dots. - Pss. 149-151 are separated from the corresponding Pss. of the Virgin by chains of black and red dots.
